'The guy was going real fast around the turns and I just didn't know why because we were making good time,' Frank Tatulli told The Sun.

Dianne Jackson backed his claim, saying: 'The driver was going around the curve really fast. Next thing you know we we're in the middle of a wreckage.'

Joel Zaritzky described the moment the train was derailed.

